text:
themagazinerolep x christina aguilera 
_______________________________________________________

trpm: hello miss. covergirl! we just want thank you for being apart of this magazine. to begin with,  we want to congratulate you on your marriage! how’s that been for you?

xtina: hello! thank you so much! it’s been totally amazing. me and enrique, as i like to call him, have been best friends and it’s always great to get to marry the one who you have closest to your heart. we have such an amazing relationship and i can always talk to him about anything. it’s really beautiful.

trpm: it’s our pleasure. and aw! a match made in heaven. you recently finished your #liberationtour just last month! how was that experience? do you miss it?

xtina: since it’s been ten years since i was on tour — in fact i was pregnant while i did the back to basics tour so, it felt great to be back onstage as well and hearing the fans singing along to some hits as well. i already miss it i must say, but i plan a world tour or at least a bigger tour next year, hopefully it will happen.

trpm: we heard! you have the best fans in the world even after years. ooh! we cannot wait for that to happen. on your new album “liberation” that you released in june, you’ve done a lot of collaborations! do you have a personal favorite and do you want to collaborate with any of them again in the near future?

xtina: i mean, i love all of them and it was extremely fun to explore and try new things and directions as well. but i have to say fall in line that i did with the amazing demi is my absolute favorite, and i’d definitely do another collab with her in the future!

trpm: ah, yes! that’s a personal favorite for us too. we’ll be looking forward to that as well. you launched hair tools with lidl on december 12th, which was yesterday. do you have a favorite? 
xtina: that’s a tough question, everyone is so great! but if i have to choose, it’s actually adore the hairdryer and the hairbrushers.

trpm: we adore the hairbrushes. your friend demi lovato and yourself have been nominated for a grammy for “best pop duo” with your song “fall in line.” how did that make you feel?

text:
i have yet to give up, and i'm not going to start now. 
whatever struggles you have had this past week, or what may come up this weekend, choose to not give up. you have what it takes, even if you dont feel like it.

you were made for greatness!

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

.

text: have been riveted by this seminal book by the ridiculously inspiring joan smith. riverrun will publish home grown, her blistering polemic on the link between domestic violence and terrorism, in 2019. it is searing, horrifying and urgent. misogynies was published in 1989 and joan kindly gave me this slightly strange looking us edition from 1992 when we met this week. its subjects have of course dated but joan’s writing is deeply incisive, the book includes truly shocking case studies and - depressingly - the malevolent influence of page 3 she eloquently criticises is now multiplied to an extent then unimaginable by the explosion of online media since. appalling, fascinating yet often funny, joan was saying then a lot of things we are still wrestling with now. her analysis of clarence thomas v anita hill has clear and depressing parallels with kavanaugh’s recent scandalous appointment and the #metoo movement thirty years later. this endless nonsense is exhausting. #joansmith #misogynies #feminism #feministbooks #readwomen #nonfic #nonfiction #nonfictionbooks #amreading #bookstagram #bookstagramuk #riverrunbooks #homegrown #domesticviolence

text:
since the banning of "baby its cold outside" in light of the #metoo movement, please boycott the christmas song "i want a hippopotamus for christmas" because it exploits endangered hippos.

while we are at it the same goes for: "santa clause is coming to town" = fake news "little drummer boy" = gender neutral "white christmas" = racist and xenophobic "o' come all ye faithful" = exclusive "god rest ye merry gentlemen" = anti-feminist "all i want for christmas is you" = stalking "blue christmas" = implies male/boy righteousness "the 12 days of christmas" = anti-semitic (8 days) "santa baby" = reverse #metoo and exploits handouts "winter wonderland" = dismisses wonderlands that don't have winter "its the most wonderful time of the year" = exclusive against 4th of july and summer "let it snow" = not fair to those where it does not snow "do you hear what i hear" = insensitive to hearing impaired "all i want for christmas is my two front teeth" = offensive to meth addicts

and last but not least.... "i saw mommy kissing santa claus" = promotes adultery

if this offends anyone, please don’t bother to tell me as i just don’t care. copy and paste if you agree!

text:
#youtube və digər sosial şəbəkələrdə məktəb porn videosunu yayan şərəfsizləri #dtx və #di̇n təcili həbs edib cəzalandırmalıdır! bu tiplər başa düşmürlər o qız və onun ailə üzvləri hansı həyacan dolu hisslər, stress və şok keçirirlər anbaan! 
qızın nənəsi artıq xəstəxanadadır, anası vot-votdadır, xalası stressdən əziyyət çəkir! 
ay binamuslar heç olmasa öz qızınızı, bacınızı, ananızı, arvadınızı düşünün! bir gün sizin də başınıza bu hadisə gələcək! nə qədər gec deyil pozun! əks halda 5-8 il #həbs! ▪️oğlan getdi sroka. ▪️qız məhkəmə tibbi ekspertizadan keçib və aşkar olunub ki, hələ də bakirədir! 
hal-hazırda evdədir! rahat buraxın reabi̇li̇tasi̇ya olunsunlar!!!! videoları yaymayın! pozun!!! allah bağışlamaz! 
kömək etmək lazimdir! qinamaq və təhgi̇r etmək yox!!! maraqlısı bilirsiz nədir? bu məsələ 2017 dekabr ayında baş verib və məktəbin müəllimləri, valideyinlər bu videonu görüb, lakin heç bir tədbir görməyiblər! laqeyd yanaşıblar və şaiyyələr yaymağa başlayıblar. qızın anasına heç kim heçnə deməyib.
müəllimlər bu hadisə ilə bağlı məktəbdə ən azı maarifləndirmə işlərini apara, uşaqlara bu işin psixoloji, mənəvi və hüquqi tərəfini başa sala bilərdilər! lakin susmaği üstün tutublar! bu da nəticə! yenə də uşaq müdafi̇əsi̇ qanunu olmadığı üçün, müəllimlər də bilmirlər nə etsinlər! united aid for azerbaijan (@uafa.az) #childprotection #uafa #metoo

birdə məni məktəbi̇n "təhlükəsi̇zli̇yi̇" məsələsi narahat edir! 
bu hall bir daha onu sübüt edir ki, məktəblərdə nəzarət, məsuliyyət və təhlükəsizlik 0 səviyyəsindədir! təsəvvür edin o otaqda və ya məktəbin digər küncündə hansısa uşağı rahatlıqla bıçaqlayıb 🔪 aradan çıxmaq olar.

text:
estos días pensé mucho en todo lo que está sucediendo; y la verdad es que yo realmente creo el relato de estas mujeres que fueron abusadas, violadas, ultrajadas, maltratadas, por hombres misóginos, machistas, asquerosos, repugnantes. el motivo, además de mi empatía con ellas por supuesto; es porque yo también conocí a un machirulo que ejerció abuso y violencia de género contra mi, hace unos años, cuando yo todavía estaba aprendiendo a defenderme. esa persona me violento, me maltrató y me hizo mucho daño como mujer y como persona. gracias a mis padres, fui educada con unos valores de decencia y dignidad muy fuertes, que me ayudaron a defenderme y a salir escapando de toda esa situación. en ese momento, como era más joven, yo no me daba cuenta de lo que pasaba, de lo que me estaba haciendo, de todo ese daño psicológico que ejercía sobre mi, y que no llegó a daño físico porque supe salir a tiempo y ponerle límites, y lo más importante, alejarme de ese sorete. pero después, con el tiempo y la información que pude ir adquiriendo, me di cuenta de que eso no había sido nada normal, que eso que yo había sufrido se llamaba abuso y violencia de género. y aprendí mucho a elegir con otra mirada mucho más inteligente, a qué tipo de personas quería acercarme y tener a mi lado. y hoy por hoy estoy muy bien acompañada, contenida, cuidada y amada. me rodean personas que buscan mi bien, y de quienes yo también pretendo su bienestar. por eso me siento identificada con esas mujeres sufridas, porque salir a la calle es todo un riesgo y un peligro; y lamentablemente, a mi también me tocó conocer un machito nefasto, ignorante y carente de corazón por completo. parece que somos muchas las mujeres que, desgraciadamente, alguna vez hemos tenido que soportar y padecer algún maltrato horrible en manos de algún tipo asqueroso y mala persona. actualmente, sólo sé que seguramente ya la está pagando, porque convivir con él mismo ya es el peor de los castigos, y además la justicia divina y el universo se encargan de hacer lo suyo. 
ahora mismo sólo puedo decir, que estoy más que segura de que cada persona recibe lo que da; y que yo decidí dar amor, para poder recibir amor. y así será siempre.❤❤

text:
for over 3 years myself and 6 others were part of an account called _homo_intended_. it was hacked at 9.7k followers, and we lost the entire account, as well as our posts, memories, and all the people who followed and interacted with us. luckily i have this account (previously @that_queer_transboy) that i changed into the new _homo_intended_. for now it will just me me and @queen_kebin running this account, but once we figure out things we may add admins. as hard as it is to lose our beloved safe space, we are back and we are not going to give up. the account was created so we can help others, advocate for our community, and have a safe space to express ourselves. a hacker tried to take that from us, but we are back now and ready to make the account even better than it was before. -dawson

text_retweet:
you have power. you have a phone. call gov. bill haslom and let him know what you think. read more below:  #repost and 🎨 @badasscrossstitch
・・・
via @cnn - cyntoia brown, who's serving life in prison for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16, could still be freed soon.
the tennessee supreme court last week ruled brown would have to serve at least 51 years in prison for the 2004 killing before she's eligible for release.
but amid widespread outrage on social media, gov. bill haslam's office is now reviewing her case. <——- proof that we can have a voice and impact. ——-
what to do now? 
1. go read about the case
2. sign the moveon petition 
3. share your thoughts and links on social media so folks know and can take action 
4. contact gov bill haslam’s office and voice your thoughts 1st floor, state capitol nashville, tn 37243 (615) 741-2001 
5. his instagram @governorbillhaslam (remember, he is considering clemency so let’s honor and encourage that) 
6. watch the video: me facing life: cyntoia’s story - google it - it’s on @pbs and you can watch it online. ——————
update:  original art by <<<< @janaillustration >>>follow her! her work is perfection. 
i have tried so hard to find out who made the original piece that i used to stitch this. if you know, please let me know so that i can cite. ——— #blacklivesmatter #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #metoo #justice #freecyntoia #clemencyforcyntoia #resist 
#blm #cyntoiabrown #pussyhatproject

text:
this post is for those who have been my seniors in school but has treated me as their own sister ❤ you have been there through all my thick and thin. right from helping me out in studies to solving my real life issues you people have played your part really well. i know my words are not enough to thank you for being in my life but thats the biggest thing i could do right now to make you guys feel special and wanted ❤ though we didn't talk much during your school days nevertheless our bond grew more stronger after you stepped out from the school..whatever you guys experienced you help me out with that experience in every possible way.you three are my real gems of life whom i don't wanna loose ever ❤ your every dedication towards me shows me how important i am as a person to you and this last year was absolutely amazing because of your existence sisters💫  i love you guys so much (samiksha di @sam_srivastava1602, alisha di @alishanegi29, divya di @divya_sharma00018) ❤ hope we travel furlongs of our lives together.
- samriddhi bisht 🐼 @samriddhibisht
.
--------×--------
.
in these times of #metoo and stories of sexual harassment, there are also women and men around us who made us feel more beautiful, more confident and powerful from both inside and out. 
if there is a person who brought some meaningful changes in your life, then let's pay a tribute to her/him right here at @shespeaksforthechange.

we all need such people around us afterall, don't we?
(dm us your story or tag us in your post.) #shespeaksforthechange

text:
colour correction är över för denna gång! nu siktar vi på indienturné 2019 och håller tummarna för att det bär!
vi vill rikta ett stort tack till alla besökare, alla lärare som bokat in sina klasser, och till uppsala stadsteater som ännu en gång upplåtit sin scen till oss!

att spela föreställningen har känt väldigt speciellt denna gång. vi har upplevt att det funnits ett lyssnande, en förståelse framför allt hos vår gymnasiepublik som kanske inte riktigt fanns förra vändan. speciellt tydligt blir det i scenerna mot slutet, där en filmproducent använder sin maktposition för att bli närgången på en provspelning, har förut mötts av de där garven som brukar komma när det mest är knäppt på scenen. den här gången är det som att skratten fastnat i halsgropen. vi tänker såklart att det handlar om #metoo-kampanjen, att det finns en annan kunskap om vad som faktiskt pågår i stor skala. också på de efterföljande samtalen har det känts att vi nu inte gör en föreställning som informerar och upplyser om ämnet, utan snarare öppnar upp för en diskussion om det. det har helt enkelt känts väldigt, väldigt bra. 
#colourcorrection #mukhamugam #bonthrop #bananteatern #förallaöverallt

text:
как остановить травлю в школе и на работе-1
в фейсбуке которую неделю бушуют страсти из-за травли сына ульяны меньшиковой @iulianamenshikova - и ее самой, вставшей на защиту своего ребенка. руководство и учителя лицея, спокойно смотревшие, как на одинокого мальчишку нападает толпа, теперь защищают юных садистов и пугают связями их родителей. и даже объединились с ними против ульяны (как будто у нее, ухаживающей за двумя тяжелобольными, мало было проблем). но меньшикова - настоящий борец! и этот «локальный» конфликт, выплеснувшись в соцсети, стал не менее важным, чем прошлогоднее движение #metoo. мужчины даже не подозревали, насколько многих женщин (практически каждую) так или иначе коснулись отвратительные домогательства, особенно в совсем юном возрасте - а то и что похуже. 
теперь нам предстоит осознать масштаб проблемы буллинга. все начинается со школы - но, на самом деле, дома. ребенок из действительно благополучной семьи не захочет издеваться над другими детьми и животными! допустим, родители сами подают дурной пример. не осознав в детстве из-за противодействия учителей, что буллинг - это совершенно неприемлемое поведение (кстати, равнодушие и попустительство педагогов сильно травмирует не только жертв, но и многочисленных маленьких свидетелей травли), подросшие психопаты выходят во взрослую жизнь. где простора для активности больше. травля на работе – не менее популярное занятие, чем в школах, хотя люди вроде бы все уже взрослые, по своему жизнью битые. знающие уже на своем личном опыте, что такое боль и страдания. и, тем не менее. 
остановить юных подонков можно: есть разработанные инструкции, куда обращаться (директор школы, потом роно и тд. подробнее - на 3 выложенных фото). #stopbullying #antibulling #буллинг #bulling #психология #япротивнасилия #travlinet #дети #ребенок #подростки #подросток #школа #семья #воспитание #учитель #работа #офис #общество #жизнь #справедливость #бог #карма #дружба #друзья #friend #friends #friendship #society #рождество

text:
как остановить травлю в школе и на работе-2
а что делать, если одиночку травит офисный «террариум единомышленников» или зловредные соседи? с последним я сама столкнулась в 2003-2005, ежедневно страдая от выходок молодых гопников, которых я осмелилась вежливо попросить курить на пол пролёта выше, т.к. я аллергик, а вся токсичная вонь от их многочасовых посиделок на лестнице шла прямиком мне в крошечную однушку. одна соседка мне как-то посочувствовала: «как же вам, наверное, тяжело», другие делали вид, что их это не касается – хотя глазки и почтовые ящики эта банда сломала практически всем. милиция порой вообще не приезжала под видом «а у нас машина сломалась», а если приезжала, то после отъезда стражей порядка становилось только хуже. мне чудом не выломали дверь (спасибо, что была железная). окна разбивали неоднократно. я так мечтала оттуда вырваться, что даже в лондон улетела ;) (подробности в моей книге «новая жизнь»). в конечном счете все, что нас не убивает, в самом деле делает сильнее. но здоровье-то не вернешь… даже мыши не могут жить в хроническом стрессе и не только начинают хворать, но и умирают. буллинг приводит не только к болезням и депрессии, но и к самоубийствам. и, опять же, травля травмирует не только жертв, но и невольных свидетелей, отравляя все вокруг.
акция #metoo, над которой поначалу смеялись не только многие мужчины, но и некоторые недалекие женщины, в итоге привела к важным изменениям в обществе. я очень надеюсь, что и #antibulling принесет свои плоды! а пока хочу поделиться очень мудрым постом (в как остановить травлю в школе и на работе-3) - касается всех руководителей! если часть ваших сотрудников объединяется против кого-то и гнобит, это не пойдет на пользу ни общей атмосфере, ни (в итоге) производительности труда. 
#stopbullying #буллинг #bulling #психология #япротивнасилия #travlinet #дети #ребенок #подростки #подросток #школа #семья #воспитание #учитель #работа #офис #общество #жизнь #справедливость #бог #карма #дружба #друзья #friend #friends #friendship #society #рождество

text:
i find it hard to photograph the iridescence of these mugs. i finally was able to capture it (swipe to see) with the new cfl light set up that @daedal_goods uses and was kind enough to share with me! .
.
.
these mugs are #sexualabuseawareness mugs. no one likes to think or discus the issue of sexual abuse but it is unfortunately something that almost every woman i know deals with and a handful of men too. i wanted this line of big ass mugs to be bright and happy, i intentionally let the “mine not yours” crack. the cracks to me represent how sexual abuse can try and destroy you, how it can break you down and leave behind wounds that can heal but will always be there. the bright and beautiful pink and crisp lines represents how woman are incredibly resilient, how no matter what is thrown at us we come together and we conquer the assaults! as a child of sexual abuse, this is a very important project for me. for every “mine not yours” mug that is purchased, a art therapy session will available to someone in need. 💕 #metoo

text: my grandmother passed away today. she suffered very much for a long time, so while losing her is painful, there is also gratitude for the end of her suffering. this loss brings up more pain from other life events, and it’s a challenge to not turn away but instead lean into the unfolding raw experiences of this life and this death, with gentleness and curiosity. there seems to simultaneously be a lot and nothing at all to say. yesterday a guy in a bar behaved very inappropriately toward me and my friend, and didn’t stop even when clearly told. in the end we got him thrown out from the bar, but he had already stepped over our boundaries several times by then. at the time, i only felt murderous anger, but afterwards i realized how deeply frightening and hurtful it had been to not have my boundaries respected. i don’t know whether it would have mattered to him or not if he’d known that i was about to face a death in my family, but i like to think that when we behave with violence towards others we do so because of our ignorance. we forget that every person we encounter will lose absolutely everything that they love including their self, and when we forget that, it’s easy to end up treating others (and ourselves) without kindness and respect. may this pain serve to help us remember to be honest with ourselves about life and how we treat the people we come across. and may we all act to bring more consciousness, warmth and curiosity into this world to heal the sources of any ignorance and coldness that we find. #metoo #timesup #death #opening #surrenderbeyondwords #radicaldharma #fuckviolence #consent #consentculture #consentlegislationnow #letsgetreal
name: Sara Kirstisdotter

text:
hypocrisy of current advocacy
#metoo #teenagepregnancy #saynotochildmarriage #educationnotexploitation #endchildlabour 
all eloquent coinages depicting decades struggles of inequality, exploitation and abuse but largely an inadequate, selfish and myopic representation of the urgency required to tackle this menace. however, the greatest obstacle to securing our rights and place in society is us, women and advocates.

proliferation of advocacy organizations
aptly, too many cooks spoil a good pudding. such a significant menace requires, nay, demand an urgent action. however, the purpose of the fight, its necessity and its possibilities has been diverted to one of money making and a matter of status. a situation to prove a humanitarian spirit that is lacking in most. an opportunity to be ceos, executive directors and chairs of foundations by people with little grasp of tools that accords them with leverage to make actual progress and change. can you as supporters of a cause not make the same impact (if not more) by aligning with other organizations with the means, methods and network? 
backbiting & battle for supremacy
the very essence of advocacy has now been diverted to mean “the one with the most fame, awards and money”. postings are now about those following trends, been the most angry about issues of abuse but then doing a disappearing act when it comes to actually supporting, funding for significant impact and initiating ventures that guarantees change. most unfortunate is the habit of rumor mongering & back biting those considered threats to their own supremacy and recognition.
the questions remain, who made advocacy about benefiting? who made it about popularity or one with most awards? 
lessons
when will women learn that this world was wired for men and padded for men and that level of comfort is promoted by women who harbor and circulate hate and misrepresentation of colleagues? 
when will women consider it their responsibility to instill goodness and gentleman behaviors at an early age onto the character of our boys who become the men who abuse us and our younger counterparts?
when will women consider it their responsibility to instill value and confide

text:
the grand temple of murudeshwara is located on the banks of the arabian sea in north karnataka. 18 storeys high, a beach with clean blue water and a gigantic statue of shiva just adjacent to the ocean makes it one of the most picturesque structures in the country.

i made it a point to visit this temple town during my goa-gokarna trip last month. for those visiting gokarna (esp people who like to click), murudeshwara is just 70-75 kms away and is one of the destinations which is too good miss. - shot on google pixel 3xl #teampixel

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult

via @manueladavila “a maior quebra de silêncio da história. até hoje, 330 mulheres se uniram para denunciar o mesmo homem. por assédio, estupro, pedofilia, incesto praticados há décadas. décadas em que cada uma delas silenciou, foi desacreditada ou ameaçada de morte. essas 330 mulheres não são loucas, mentirosas, invejosas. elas são vítimas. vítimas de um homem poderoso que usa deus como sobrenome. elas são vítimas de séculos de silenciamento. mas o tempo das mulheres chegou. empoderadas por todas as denúncias que vieram antes, no brasil e no mundo, elas decidiram se unir e falar. é hora de investigar e punir quem tiver que ser punido. é hora de justiça. parabéns pela coragem de todas as mulheres envolvidas nesta histórica quebra de silêncio. nós estamos com vocês”

text: so many great things have happened since the #metoo movement first started a little over a year ago. we wouldn’t be in this moment without the incredibly brave silence breakers- the women and men who spoke out and named an abuser.  i know that i’m in a very fortunate position with my career right now, but that’s not the case for a lot of people who have been integral in this movement. most have been pushed down in our business (or out altogether), which is sickening since we know that if they had just complied or remained silent, they might be at the top of the town today. they spoke out, and because of the power and support of social media, the people who run this industry have been forced to make changes. their names should be the ones headlining movies. they should be given the opportunities to do award-nominating work. they should be paid top dollar. and anyone in a position to elevate them should do it.

text:
i've been thinking about the process of healing lately. partly, because meghan and i have been going through a process of healing, but also many new and old friends are going through their own journeys.

healing is a process that never ends. the trauma changes us. it redirects us to new places. sometimes our journeys are interrupted by new trauma or by forms of coping that hurt us more. 
almost every week, something challenges meghan and i in a new way. that sets us back. i live with the constant fear that the next something will throw us back into the chaos and hopelessness of a couple years ago. 
far too often in my life, my weakness has allowed fear to shut me down, to let that fear win. fear divides us, it turns some of us into monsters. 
how do we overcome that fear? maybe, not overcome. how do we keep the momentum of healing? 
love. hope. relation. being heard, being seen. some days, our healing is a personal journey. sometimes our trauma demands isolation. but there will always be a time that our hurt needs to be heard, seen, validated, and healed through the ways we relate to others. 
that, to me, is how we need to envision community. trauma may have ended a part of me, but healing has given me a way to see through this, together. 
what does your heart and head need to heal? how do we create a society in which cycles of trauma aren't the norm?

text: #youdoyou. sounds easy, right. guess what, it isn't. people love to throw phrases around that they read on facebook. feel the #meaning behind it? no. i heard this and other phrases before, but i'm just slowly learning to actually feel them. it's a long #journey i'm on, but it's the right one. you'll have #collateraldamage along the way of #selfdiscovery my #therapist told me. my social workers asked me to be cautious of possible bachkash i might receive when i stand my ground. open up to my feelings, voicing my needs. they were right. i knew in the back of my head as well. #selfsacrifice is what i did all my life. living the life for others than myself. besides my parents nobody actually demanded this... well, maybe my #ex. but seriously: fack him. sure, i let that #sexualabuse happen. sure,  i let #mentalabuse happen, but i never asked for it. also i never asked anybody to take advantage of me or my situation. i'm learning that it's ok to be angry. it's ok to admit being a #victim. i am not #desperate anymore. i am not ashamed anymore. yet, strangely i still feel the need to explain myself. still afraid people won't believe me. a lot of people do, but #rape, #sexualabuse is such a sensitive topic many don't understand. are scared of even, because this is something that doesn't happen in their life. they shut it out. for me, it is reality. when the #metoo movement started, i was like yeah. i thought i was alone with that. i am male, how could this happen to me? the truth is, the #abuse starts with a no. if it doesn't end there, it's #abuse. i want and am getting better. holding on...

via @cnn - cyntoia brown, who's serving life in prison for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16, could still be freed soon.
the tennessee supreme court last week ruled brown would have to serve at least 51 years in prison for the 2004 killing before she's eligible for release.
but amid widespread outrage on social media, gov. bill haslam's office is now reviewing her case. <——- proof that we can have a voice and impact. ——-
what to do now? 
1. go read about the case
2. sign the moveon petition 
3. share your thoughts and links on social media so folks know and can take action

text_retweet:
✊🏼chiming in the #meettosleep spirit: #repost @jugniology with ・・・
since the time i came across the #meettosleep initiative, my mind kept breezing past my childhood years when we would sleep in the parks during family picnics or on the terrace during summers. it seemed like a memory from an archived past.
💤 💤 💤 
meet to sleep , invites women and individuals to take a nap in their public parks. the event takes place in multiple location along with individual action heroes, partners and allies. through sleep, meet to sleep participants, or action heroes assert the right to live free from fear, warnings and blame. the event last three hours and is followed by an
exchange on the experience.
😴 😴 😴 
join me for #meettosleep2018
date: december 16, 2018
time: 2 pm to 5 pm
location: thane (dm and you will be sent registration details)
.
.
.
it’s time we fight fear, we're taught to carry. this year we meet to sleep, in memory of jyoti singh, also known to the world as #nirbhaya, the fearless one. jyoti singh was gangraped and murdered on december 16th, 2012. we also #meettosleep remembering all those who said #metoo and #niunamenos. this year, we #meettosleep remembering our own experiences. we #meettosleep in solidarity. we sleep remembering what we know, and the stories that are yet to be told. (source: @blanknoiseactionheroes)

.
a boneca amora metoo tem olhos com toques de brilho, bochechas rosadas, trancinhas no cabelo e uma roupa fofa. além de ser companhia inseparável da criança a todo momento é também um item de decoração.
esta boneca charmosa é um presente perfeito para qualquer menina em qualquer data! as bonequinhas metoo são super fofas vão marcar a infância das crianças.
caracteristicas do produto:
✔️composição 100% poliéster, enchimento 100% fibra de poliéster. .
✔️lavar com sabão neutro e água fria. .
✔️não alvejar. não lavar à máquina. ✔️validade indeterminada. ✔️indicação de idade: a partir de 3 meses. ✔️conheça todos os modelos das bonecas metoo, você vai se encantar e querer ficar com todas. 😍😍😍
✔️fabricante metto.
*consulte valor de frete.
.
▶️de r$109,90 por r$99,00 via depósito ou transferência bancária. .
▶️de r$129,90 por r$119,90 via pagseguro. . .

text: i was born with a strong desire to live in the country, a tomboy through and through. a love for fishing, hunting and gettin my hands dirty. for the last 26 years i was living that dream - i’m a country girl. seven months ago i had to step out of my comfort zone and move back to my hometown in the bay area. kicking and screaming i made the move. today - i can honestly say i am the happiest i’ve ever been, knowing i’m right where i’m suppose to be......for now. just because life interrupted doesn’t mean it’s the end of my story. i’m not giving up on my dream - my desire to live in the country is still strong. god has a plan and i trust him completely. i may have been moved out of my comfort zone but i’m so glad i did! my expectant hope is back! never give up y’all and enjoy the race called life. #countrygirl #hope #faith #joy #love #myblinddatewithgod #life #bigcity #trust #metoo #victim #survivor #dreams #nevergiveup #countrystrong #414ministry #acquitted #goodtimes #race #desires #jesus #savior

text: someone recently reached out to me about a bulk order of these pins. she shared her #metoo story with me and it broke my heart. i designed these pins before the 2016 election, before #metoo , in a different headspace in a different world. i was so sad to hear her story but i was elated that she related so much to this pin and that she truly felt empowered. i cannot believe the politics of today but the best we can do is stay woke, vote with your dollar, volunteer, and talk to each other. donating to causes near and dear and buying a stranger a coffee will also probably help the world be a better place ☕️

text:
🧿{r-i-t-u-a-l-s}🧿
.
 what are your rituals?
.
a ritual is a ceremony, a practice, an act of worship. but what are we honoring in our rituals? in our daily practices? are we celebrating what serves us, or do we make too much time for thoughts and habits and people that detract from our highest selves?
. 
my rituals: crisp morning runs. cooking while listening to podcasts. a compulsion to randomly text people if i think of them (sorry ~ that explains the random texts) 💁🏻‍♂️
.
i’m not up here on a soapbox - my rituals also include toxic self-sabotage, inescapable self-doubt, and crippling indecision, at times. they include eating nacho cheese doritos with plain yogurt, a holdover from childhood that my sister and i came to love. we have a dorito dance. everyone should have a dorito dance 🕺🏻🤸🏾‍♂️💃🏻
. 
my rituals include a gratitude practice. every morning, i write down three things i'm thankful for and something i'm proud of. some days, the thoughts flow effortlessly, and my pen barely keeps up. other days, i feel tightness. resistance. disdain. emotional stinginess. i used to fight that. i've learned to allow that part of me to exist, as well. to make space for it. to honor it 🙏🏽
.
the poet rumi writes that the human being is a "guest house" where "every morning there is a new arrival. a joy. a depression. a meanness. welcome and entertain them all. the dark thought. the shame. the malice. meet them at the door laughing and invite them in. they may be clearing you out for some new delight." 🏡❤️
.
ok, so i'm no rumi...but i do try to sit with whatever it is coming up in my life. i took a private voice lesson the other day and my teacher said, "whatever it is that comes up in your voice, honor that. not with volume, but with intention." holy shit, i thought...what a beautiful maxim. "not with volume, with intention." so many parts of my life could benefit from that notion🤩🤯
.
but in the end life is meant to be enjoyed. so, fuck it, grab the doritos and do your own damn dance ✨😎💫
.
📸 @jjreddington 🙏🏽🙌🏽
.
#doritos #dance #graitude #practice #grace #rumi #nyc #newyork #photography #photographer #newyorkcity #tattoo #tattoos #ink

text:
zeitreise
es ist donnerstag, der 15. dezember 2016. mein freund max und ich haben uns urlaub genommen, er hat sogar geburtstag. wir liefen hand in hand durch #ludwigshafen. man hätte meinen können, wir seien ein ganz normales paar auf einem spaziergang.

die #wahrheit war: ich hatte angst. ganz furchtbare angst. ich wusste, dass dieser tag, dieser „spaziergang“ mein leben verändern würde. ich hatte ja keine ahnung, wie sehr! 
ich ging zum ersten mal meinen wege. ich ging, um mich für mich einzusetzen. ich ging, um das richtige zu tun. mir schlug das herz wie wild in der brust. ich hörte das blut in meinen ohren rauschen. ich spürte die warme hand meines freundes in meiner.

es war mein gang zum #polizeipräsidium ludwigshafen. ich hatte eine vorladung, ich sollte gegen den mann aussagen, den ich in der woche zuvor wegen „schweren sexuellen missbrauchs minderjähriger“ angezeigt habe. dieses behördendeutsch klingt so abstrus, so weit weg vom eigentlichen geschehen, und dennoch ist es irgendwie beruhigend für das geschehene worte zu finden.

das unaussprechliche aussprechen zu können. 14 jahre lang habe ich geschwiegen. aus angst. aus angst, er würde all seine drohungen wahr machen. aus angst, mir würde niemand glauben. aus angst, meine eltern würden mich nicht mehr liebe. aus angst, angst und noch mehr #angst.

die zeit der angst war endlich vorbei. ich war 25 jahre alt - eine erwachsene frau. mr. arschloch kann mir gar nichts mehr. all diese ängste gehörten der kleinen, süßen 10-jährige mai mit 2 zöpfchen. die große, erwachsene mai wusste, dass sie mit der anzeige die machtverhältnisse nun ein für alle mal umdrehen wird. sie braucht keine angst mehr haben. nicht mehr schweiß gebadet aufwachen. sie hat nichts falsches gemacht, sondern er - mr. arschloch.

nach 3 sehr zermürbenden und tränen reichen stunden vernehmung, bin ich glücklich und stolz und ein klein wenig zittern aus dem polizeigebäude geschwankt. die hand meines freundes fest umgriffen. beim gedanken an diesen moment kommen mir jetzt beim schreiben immer noch die tränen…
.
.
.
#metoo #mutausbruch #aufschrei #feminismus #victimblaming

.

text:
since the beginning of time many things have changed and have been reformed in every area of our lives. 
to make change you have to change. the ones who can-will. the ones who can’t, will eventually be helped to changed, forced to change, or simply phase out. you don’t see horse and buggies on our freeways. you don’t see coal driven trains. the majority of the world welcomes evolution and change. 
if you are disturbed by what you are seeing-what girls and women go thru and you are saddened by it-don’t be. 
this is the first time in history the entire planet is falling into agreement....the way women are spoken to and treated has to change. if you feel weak, don’t worry, those of us who found a way to speak and to help other women...have your back. if you are paralyzed in fear...don’t worry. there are women speaking on your behalf and protesting and standing up for all women at home and in the workplace to educate, reform and empower all parties.

if your a woman and you don’t care or it’s not an interest for you, it’s ok, women are still banding together worldwide to change the epidemic of women being abused in every possible way.

we want to save the animals and the oceans and have the best technology. let’s look across the room, the table, the store, the hallway, the workplace, the yard and help each other. 
this is not a battle against men. this is women saying “enough.” this is not a gender war. this is women saying “it can be different”. i have four daughters and my past was abusive. i have spent years on the front lines and at home teaching and educating my daughters and my friends and any women who will listen about self value.

i will never stop. it is not up to men if we value ourselves. it’s not up to them if they think we are attractive, have nice asses or are friendly enough. that’s not what makes us anymore. not even the labels they put on us...the names they call us...or any of it.  if we want to be sexy, we are being sexy for ourselves not for a mans approval. 
we have a new year coming. when you celebrate the holidays this end of 2018, thank a woman. thank many women. say thank you for doing your part.

text:
les réseaux sociaux sont devenus un support pour combattre l’hyper-sexualisation de la femme, un moyen de combattre leurs propres dérives... ce paradoxe et cette nouvelle perspective peuvent d’abord être soulignés au travers de la lutte contre les violences sexuelles, impact direct de cette image hyper-sexualisée de la femme sur les rapports hommes/femmes 
nous pouvons voir cela via le mouvement #metoo

en octobre 2017 démarre l’affaire harvey weinstein, révélation de harcèlements et d'agressions sexuelles par cette personnalité influente de l'industrie du cinéma américain.
cela a de nombreuses conséquences, avec une série d’accusation du monde politique, médiatique et artistique. 
cette affaire donne lieu à un débat débat plus large sur les violences faites aux femmes et leur occultation, au travers du statut des femmes dans la société. 
l’actrice, productrice et activiste américaine alyssa milano est à l’initiative du hashtag #metoo, qui a permis de libérer la parole des victimes de harcèlement et d’agressions sexuelles, d’abord sur twitter. femmes et hommes, célébrités et anonymes, ont participé à la diffusion du message. 
c’est un phénomène devenu mondial...
le #metoo devient  #أنا كمان ("ana kamane", moi aussi) dans les pays arabes, #yotambien dans les pays hispanophones, #balancetonporc 
en france, #quellavoltache en italie... bien sûr, comme nous le montre la carte il ne s’est pas exporté de la même manière partout dans le monde.
mais nous avons ce passage du «je», au «elle aussi», et finalement au «nous toutes»... il s’est aussi exporté hors des réseaux sociaux ! 
le magazine le monde parle de «mouvement social féminin du xxie siècle». ce n’est pas un phénomène seulement viral donc, destiné à se diluer... mais il est question de repenser la question du rapport entre les sexes, de la violence, faire valoir ses droits! 
cela s’est vu lors de manifestations, et a aussi impacté le monde politique, qui ne peut plus ignorer ce problème majeur de société. 
bien sur, cela n’est que le début d’un lent processus.

text:
the next time i hold my pen
i promise,
i won't let my words meet you
the horizon, maybe
not you.
but today i let them loose
turns out,
you're the ruler 
they crave to slave for. 
funny how,
my definition of love went from
prince charming with perfect smile
to goofy grin with unkempt stubble;
or maybe i should just 
write my own fairytale,
only that my prince charming has
crooked tooth
and his eyes do not twinkle
'like stars in a midnight sky'
my own fairytale,
only that the princess is not
a damsel in distress 
but a hopeless romantic 
playing around with imperfect words
until they make sense 
my own fairytale,
only that cinderella's shoe
may not always fit
but her words do. 
but, 
this is the last time 
i say that,
because,
the next time i hold my pen
i promise,
i won't let my words meet you
the moon, maybe
not you.
or maybe that's what i'll say 
the next time,
and the next 
and the next 
until i'm finally 
out of love.
.
.
shruti singh.
(@the.pragmatic.idiot)
.
.
.

text: #metoo, el slogan acuñado por la activista tarana burke en 2006 y transformado en un hashtag viral por la actriz alyssa milano luego de que estalló el escándalo de weinstein, ha sido tuiteado más de 18 millones de veces en los últimos 12 meses. el movimiento ha derribado las carreras de otros hombres poderosos, incluyendo a bill cosby, kevin spacey, el director brett ratner, el candidato republicano al senado, roy moore y el director ejecutivo de cbs les moonves. esto provocó una protesta en la alfombra roja en cannes; una hoja de cálculo de google de colaboración abierta que expuso el abuso en la industria de los medios de comunicación; y una portada de la persona del año de la revista time dedicada a “los que rompen el silencio”. sobre todo, ha sido el catalizador para la tan esperada reevaluación del acoso sexual en el lugar de trabajo, un asunto que resuena más allá de los confines de hollywood.

text:
for those who have asked what i want for the holidays, honestly: 
clemency for cyntoia brown

yes, it is just one case in a larger flawed justice system where there is work to be done, but i believe this case represents a bigger truth of american history.

as this story resurges now and again over the years, many people say, “how can this happen to a child?” “how can the system have failed her so terribly?” this brings to mind the work “contested relations: slavery, sex, and medicine” where dr. deirdre cooper owens unpacks the cultural and legal ways that, during american slavery and after, there was no such concept as rape or consent for black women or girls (unless they as “property” were damaged, which created an economic case for their owners tied to reproduction). black women and girls were seen as sexual and laboring objects, not whole humans deserving of consent, affirmation of emotional trauma, and acknowledgement of abuse — let alone justice. these are the very values that were built into our justice system. imagine being a child having nowhere to go for support other than your community rendered powerless. here we are 200 years later with those very values still subversively and clearly present in the court, in medical practice, etc.

there is so much to say about this case, but it is not just cyntoia brown, it is many lesser known stories of women and girls. it is part of the american story.

please contact the office of governor bill haslam (who is reviewing the case) at ✉️ 1st floor state capital nashville, tn 37243 or 📞 615-741-2001 or @governorbillhaslam 
you can also sign the moveon petition

about the case:
cyntoia brown was a 16 year old child being sex trafficked in 2004 when tried as an adult for the murder of a man who paid to rape her. last week, tennessee supreme court ruled that she will serve at least 51 years in prison before being eligible for release. you can watch “me facing life: cyntoia’s story” for a deeper understanding.

#cyntoiabrown #believewomen #believeblackwomen #metoo #justice #socialjustice #sexworkerrights #protectchildren #healthartactivism #thisisamerica #blm #clemencyforcyntoia

text:
doesn’t everyone cry at graduations?!?
or just us “emotional” creatures. 
i look over at my almost 7year old and she is tearful/crying and smiling the whole time. i hug her and she cries more. she says “mom i’m not sad, but i’m crying?!?” why?! i had the opportunity to explain to her that some of us feel emotions much deeper than other people. and tears come out for many reasons.

i told her that it is a gift to be confident with these emotions and not try to hid them. people will try to convince you to hide them or minimize them.

please sweet girl don’t believe them. 
we need emotional creatures to love more people. 
@mrs.weir88 you made us so proud.

#emotionsareamazing #tearsofjoy #emotionalcreature #metoo 
#amazingday #nursinggraduation

text:
esta semana no fue como cualquier otra. el martes estaba arriba del auto actualizando las noticias para saber que se iba a decir en la conferencia de @actrices.argentinas
y al leer el relato una angustia enorme me agarró que no pude terminar de leerlo. al día siguiente, tuve que contener las lágrimas de emoción al leer que las líneas de atención a mujeres habían desbordado, abrir las redes y verlas llenas de valientes que después de muchos años se animaron a hablar. imposible no conmoverse.

a mí también me tocaron en el colectivo, me dijeron cosas en la calle que por miedo me hicieron cruzar de vereda, en un trabajo pasado me dijeron "acá por quién te vas a arrodillar"....si eso mismo. he visto mujeres avanzar rápidamente en puestos y en los pasillos escuchar "es que es la amante del gerente/supervisor/jefe" y también escuché historias de que perdieron el trabajo por no acceder a garchar con el jefe.

estoy esperanzada que una nueva etapa como sociedad estamos comenzando, donde mujeres y varones seamos tratados con igualdad. 
les dejo un extracto del discurso de @oprah que hoy más que nunca está vigente: "así que quiero decirle a todas esas chicas que miran televisión desde casa que un nuevo día se acerca. y cuando ese nuevo día comience será porque miles de mujeres, muchas de ellas aquí presentes, y algunos hombres fenomenales, nos acercaron un poco más al momento en que nadie tenga ya que decir nunca más yo también." #miracomonosponemos 
#noesno
#metoo
💚💚💚 ilustración tomada prestada desde @pinterestargentina

as this 2018 🖤🤘is very soon coming to a close, it’s time to post this! 
dropped off social media early this year, posting only once in awhile, why? social media is no longer a social thing, a place to connect, a place to be happy for each other’s life experiences & events, but rather, marketing strategies, where authenticity is quite questionable, to play on your emotions to sell their products or services, a place of hating on, a place where people live their lives in the image of others instead of building on their own...lessons learnt in 2018 ✍️ get out!!! of anywhere where you don’t feel good in or are treated unfairly, when you go through a hard time, do take the time to take care of you & slowly get back up, becoming stronger, working on being the best you can be, and « live a private life » keeping your circle ⭕️ who are there for you, who wish you happiness & celebrate 🎊 you!!! when you surround yourself with positivity, positive things happen in your life!! when you stay in negative 👎 being surrounded with hatred, envy & abuse, it only destroys you, your dreams, your view of life! 
this life does have so much for you, so much love for you, your own beautiful story, just stay in the light of positivity 💡 and you will see it clearly!! reach for your stars⭐️✨!!!
#positivevibes #positivity #surroundyourselfwithpositivepeople #surroundyourselfwithgoodpeople #goafteryourdreams #getout #loveyourself #metoo

text:
since the time i came across the #meettosleep initiative, my mind kept breezing past my childhood years when we would sleep in the parks during family picnics or on the terrace during summers. it seemed like a memory from an archived past.
💤 💤 💤 
meet to sleep , invites women and individuals to take a nap in their public parks. the event takes place in multiple location along with individual action heroes, partners and allies. through sleep, meet to sleep participants, or action heroes assert the right to live free from fear, warnings and blame. the event last three hours and is followed by an
exchange on the experience.
😴 😴 😴 
join me for #meettosleep2018
date: december 16, 2018
time: 2 pm to 5 pm
location: thane (dm and you will be sent registration details)
.
.
.
it’s time we fight fear, we're taught to carry. this year we meet to sleep, in memory of jyoti singh, also known to the world as #nirbhaya, the fearless one. jyoti singh was gangraped and murdered on december 16th, 2012. we also #meettosleep remembering all those who said #metoo and #niunamenos. this year, we #meettosleep remembering our own experiences. we #meettosleep in solidarity. we sleep remembering what we know, and the stories that are yet to be told. (source: @blanknoiseactionheroes)

.

text:
@regran_ed from @elishaattai -  thank you guys for coloring my birthday  positively this morning with such impactful awareness walk #womendecide in partnership with yali lagos team to pass across the message of women's crucial role in electoral decision making.

like i said earlier, african women involvement in politics and leadership will not just benefits women alone, but the continent as a whole.

the enlightened women of africa in partnership with the enlightened men will change and disrupt the system.

thank you once again to my tireless team, awlo members, yali lagos, the distinguished speakers, cadbury nigeria and our media partners!@yaliwestafrica @yalinetworklag @awloint @stbensonimoh @ebakpakpan @nkajimangewe @aitonlineng @ltvsocial @vanguardnews @tribuneonlineng @guardiannigeria - #regrann

text:
‘wir brauchen gelingende fight moves, um „why have there been no great women artists?“ (linda nochlin) zu einer historischen frage zu machen. 2018 ist sie noch erschreckend aktuell.

jessica bennett schlägt in ihrem buch „feminist fight club: a survival manual for a sexist workplace“ (2016) folgende fight moves vor:

1. help each other!*
(*„there’s a special place in hell for women who don’t help each other!”, said madeleine albright 
2. hire each other! (get more of us in power!) 3. pass on your wisdom!
(help the next generation rise up! learn from them!) ich würde dem gern hinzufügen wollen:

4. never fight each other.
(ob feministin der ersten, zweiten, dritten oder vierten welle: nur gemeinsam sind wir stark.)’ yvonne zindels kommentar zur #metoo #dicksoup #pimmelsuppe debatte in deutschland.

text:
@regran_ed from @nana_sanclemente -  el pasado diciembre 11 la actriz argentina thelma fardin @soythelmafardin hizo publica la denuncia sobre acceso carnal violento contra al actor juan darthes mientras rodaba la gira de la tan popular serie “patito feo” de la cual ambos eran cast members. la actriz tendría 16 años de edad mientras que el actor (y único adulto de la gira) tendría aproximadamente 45. al momento del encuentro y antes de la violación, el actor toma su mano y la acerca a su pantalón diciendo “mira como me pones”. nueve años le tomo a su víctima reunir la fuerza para denunciarle. ahora somos un movimiento gigante latinoamericano, empoderando la acción de levantar la voz como lo hizo thelma. ha sido tan impactante para mi como espectadora y mujer quien creció viendo la televisión argentina este episodio, que hoy me uno como ilustradora a su causa. 💚 #miracomonosponemos juan. mira que ya no tenemos miedo. ya jamas nadie se saldrá con la suya. mira como nos ponemos patriarcado. #niunamas ! #noesno !. @actrices.argentinas .

on december 11, 2018, the argentinean teen actress thelma fardin made public a criminal complaint against actor juan darthés for abuse and rape in nicaragua in 2009, events that occurred when the actress was 16 at the time and darthés 45. before the rape, the actor takes her hand and place it in his pants saying “look how you got me”. it took nine years for the victim to gather courage and denounce his actions. now we are a huge latin american movement of people who is willing to empower the action of speaking up just like thelma did. this event has taken such an impact in me as a woman and as an spectator who grew up watching argentinian series that i today i join the cause 💚 “look how you got us”, juan. look, we are not afraid anymore. look how you got us patriarchy. #nomeansno !.

text:
my fourth and final person of 2018… dr. christine blasey ford, the strong and courageous woman who spoke up during the brett kavanaugh confirmation to the us supreme court. she should be the face of the whole #metoo movement.

right from the moment that trump picked kavanaugh to be his new supreme court justice, something didn’t feel right about the guy. his views were a little bit too ‘conservitive’ and during the confirmation hearings, he mostly spoke down in a condescending manner to any of the democrat female senators who were interviewing him. but i told myself that the only reason i didn’t like him was because he was trump’s pick. maybe i should give him a chance?

then came the explosive allegation that he sexually assaulted christine when they were in high school. i still hesitated to pass judgement. both she and kavanaugh were called to testify at a hearing in front of the senate… so i watched, and seeing christine up there, in front of the whole world giving her testimony, all i could think was; what a brave and courageous woman. i knew without any doubt that she was 100% telling the truth. she didn’t have to be there, in fact, she wanted to remain anonymous. but there she was, performing her civil duty.
kavanaugh’s testimony, by comparison was sloppy and it was scripted. he let emotions like anger and impatience get the better of him, lashing out at some of the senators (a trait that you do not want to see in a sitting supreme court justice), almost like he felt that he was entitled to be a justice. i didn’t believe him for one second! absolute clown.

but in the end, it was all for nought as he still got confirmed. and trump made it a thing to go around after the confirmation and rub it in the faces of the democrats that his guy won. like it was all a game.
christine still gets death threats from ignorant idiotic trump supporters… like it was all for nothing. well, i for one will never forget her courageousness or her sense to do what is right.

i wish more people would take a page from the book of dr. christine blasey ford, who in my opinion stuck to her principals and has true strength of character! you go girl! you have earned my reverence too 👍.

what do you think about the controversy about a song you sung - "baby it's cold outside?" .
.

text:
كيف تعكس الكتب غير القصصية صعود حركة #metoo

بقلم: روبن كيرخوف
29 يونيو 2018

ترجمة: عبير علاو. @abeeer__20
التدقيق اللغوي: عبد الله علي. @3bd8llah

على الرغم من كل ما يصاحب مصطلح "النسوية" من التباسٍ وسوء فهمٍ شائع، إلا أن عام 2017 كان -بلا شك- عامًا مهما للمرأة بل لكل شخصٍ في هذا العالم بأجمعه، بعد مسيرة النساء التي عقدت في واشنطن في الحادي والعشرين من شهر يناير والتي على إثرها أعلنت مجلة التايم عن شخصية العام لعام 2017 وهم ما أسمتهم بِـ "the silence breakers of #metoo" أي محطمي الصمت التابعين لحركة #metoo وهم النساء والرجال الذين اتخذوا إجراءات ضد الرجال الأقوياء المتهمين بالتحرش الجنسي والاعتداء في عام 2017.

وحركة #metoo كانت بدايتها حملةً شعبيةً انطلقت في عام 2016 على يد الناشطة الاجتماعية تارانا بيرك، والتي كانت تهدف من تأسيس هذه الحركة أن توفر منتدى وحلقة نقاشٍ خاصةٍ بالنساء اللواتي نجون من أي شكلٍ من أشكال العنف الجنسي.

في الخامس من أكتوبر لعام 2017 أطلق وسم #metoo في وسائل الإعلام الرئيسية بعد أن ظهرت العشرات من ادعاءات الاعتداء الجنسي ضد منتج هوليوود هارفي وينشتاين والعديد من الشخصيات المشهورة والبارزة في مجالات الترفيه والأخبار والسياسة والتكنولوجيا. "يجب أن تكون نظريتك النسوية: أنا قضية هامة"
chimamanda ngozi adichie, dear ijeawele

قد يتساءل العديد من الأشخاص الآن: لماذا استغرق الأمر وقتًا طويلاً حتى يتحدث الناس عن مدى انتشار التحرش الجنسي والاعتداء على النساء؟

وللإجابة عن هذا السؤال سنستعرض بعضًا من الإصدارات والكتب والدراسات التي تشرح مدى كون هذا الموضوع متشابكٍ ومعقد.

ففي كتاب "الرجال يشرحون لي الأشياء" توضح ريبيكا سولنيت كيف يتم تشويه صورة المرأة بشكلٍ قاسٍ ومتعمدٍ في المجمتع بل أنه كثيرًا ما يتم نبذ النساء ووصفهن بالهوس حينما يتحدثن عن عدم المساواة أو الإيذاء الجنسي وقد يصل الأمر لأن يُتهمن بتقديم اتهاماتٍ باطلةٍ وكل ذلك ما هو إلا محاولةً من المعتدين لإبعاد الشكوك عنهم وإظهار أنفسهم كضحايا هذه المسألة.

وتدعم ذلك دراسةً أجراها مكتب النائب العام في المملكة المتحدة في عام 2013 والتي أوضحت إنه من بين إدعاءات الاغتصاب البالغ عددها 6551 تهمة التي تم التحقيق فيها، كان هناك فقط 35 بلاغ خاطئ وهو ما يعادل أقل من 1 في المئة.

وفي حال استمرارنا بإلقاء الشكوك على مصداقية المرأة في هذا الأمر؛ فإن العنف الجنسي سيستمر وستسكت ضحايا الاعتداء الجنسي تبعًا لذلك مما سيؤثر على التحكم بالأمر.

الشخصيات المشهورة والبارزة في مجالات الترفيه والأخبار والسياسة والتكنولوجيا . `` يجب أن تكون نظريتك النسوية : أنا قضية هامة '' chimamanda ngozi adichie , dear ijeawele قد يتساءل العديد من الأشخاص الآن متشابكٍ ومعقد . ففي كتاب `` الرجال يشرحون لي الأشياء '' توضح ريبيكا سولنيت كيف يتم تشويه صورة المرأة بشكلٍ قاسٍ ومتعمدٍ في المجمتع بل أنه كثيرًا ما يتم نبذ النساء ووصفهن بالهوس حينما يتحدثن عن عدم text:
via @cnn - cyntoia brown, who's serving life in prison for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16, could still be freed soon.
the tennessee supreme court last week ruled brown would have to serve at least 51 years in prison for the 2004 killing before she's eligible for release.
but amid widespread outrage on social media, gov. bill haslam's office is now reviewing her case. <——- proof that we can have a voice and impact. ——-
what to do now? 
1. go read about the case
2. sign the moveon petition 
3. share your thoughts and links on social media so folks know and can take action 
4. contact gov bill haslam’s office and voice your thoughts 1st floor, state capitol nashville, tn 37243 (615) 741-2001 
5. his instagram @governorbillhaslam (remember, he is considering clemency so let’s honor and encourage that) 
6. watch the video: me facing life: cyntoia’s story - google it - it’s on @pbs and you can watch it online. ——————
update:  original art by <<<< @janaillustration >>>follow her! her work is perfection. 
i have tried so hard to find out who made the original piece that i used to stitch this. if you know, please let me know so that i can cite. ——— #blacklivesmatter #feminism #feminist #craftivism #craftivist #metoo #justice #freecyntoia #clemencyforcyntoia #resist 
#blm #cyntoiabrown

.

text:
and that's a wrap! our ceo @serena__holmes is winding down her year as vp of programming for @ama_toronto. since january, she has had the pleasure of leading a team of volunteers to plan and promote a series of 10 events.

the year concluded with this past weeks packed event "looking ahead at the 2019 marketing landscape" with speakers from @acuityads.inc, @deloittecanada, @moneris.solutions, @fcb_six & @havascanada.

other amazing topics included:
🌟️ a charity incubator in support of @camptrillium,
🌟fall networking and a look at a study on customer experience in canada presented by tmg,
🌟creativity: inspiration, innovation & ideation,
⭐a @bumble_canada bizz marketing mixer,
🌟the annual cmo event,
🌟making moves in your marketing career,
⭐cannabis is coming,
🌟the impact of the #metoomovement on marketing,
⭐a fireside chat with frank palmer from @ddbcanada.

thank you to all of the speakers who contributed their time to be part of the events as well as our event partners @envillecatering, @sipbar, @revivalbartoronto, @sidlee_official, @twitter, @labatt & @bensimonbyrne.

if you're not familiar with the ama, check them out! there are monthly events for the independent marketer including excellent courses and programs such as the executive digital transformation course coming up in january as well as the mentor exchange.
.
#amatoronto #marketing #events

text:
we should be begging,  begging indigenous and first nations peoples to teach us everything they know about living in harmony with #nature 
humans are after all, just another animal on the tree of life. an animal that poisons it's own home. right now, on the ground in the amazon rainforest of ecuador, there's an emergency that will affect every single human being on the planet and not to mention all of sentient life.

with the help of the @pachamamaorg the sápara have prevented oil extraction in their territory for the past 20 years!! that's a hurculean feat. we owe them a debt of #gratitude. 
unfortunately the government of ecuador recently sold new concessions to the peruvian national oil company, for extraction of oil from their lands. the consequences are potentially fatal for the entire world. they're literally going to destroy the lungs of the earth.

collectively we're going to have to transform the behavior responsible for continuing to drive the destruction of the amazon rainforest. from the sápara perspective, many of the challenges that humanity is suffering from are due to people not remembering where they come from & being disconnected from the dreams they have each night. meaning our dreams connect us to the collective unconscious, the realm in which we are all one and connected. 
the @pachamamaorg and the sápara are working to awaken people so that they can see the possibility for and create collective change around the world.  this partnership is critical for both keeping oil development from their lands and for creating a future that works for everybody.

every species is interconnected in the biosphere and the rainforest plays a large part on this planet for keeping the air breathable. when i think of all our good works in the #metoo movement and in #antiracist work, it would all be for naught without a livable planet to share. 
please consider donating either on a regular monthly basis or a one-time donation to the @pachamamaorg  it's urgent. ( you can donate with trust. they manage all contributions to the alliance with the highest level of financial integrity and willl keep you informed about how your resources are used. )

text: kender i det med at man virkelig savner en bog eller en tv-serie, når den er slut? det er snart længe siden jeg så #betterthings på @hbonordic af @pamelaadlon og #louisck - så sjov (og så sand!)... og jeg savner den! næste omgang lader vente på sig på grund af noget #metoo halløj i hollywood... så til da leder jeg efter noget andet... og... i aftes fandt jeg den sjoveste nye franske serie på @netflixnordic ... “hvad hjertet vil!”... og... i juleferien skal jeg og en flok drenge se #vikings igen fra start... det er en vild filmatisering og #historychannel stod oprindeligt bag... dvs rigtig meget er historisk korrekt (vi sad og slog op på nettet og i saxos danmarkshistorie - anbefaler den nye udgave)... hvad ser du? hvad vil du anbefale?

text:
it was alone in bed that  i first knew.
my mind looped over and over what he did. in the quiet darkness with no escape and no distractions i finally listened.
my stomach felt sick as my mind replayed each time he raped me. it’s three years later an instead of sleeping my brain still tells me the same nightmare.
i can say i’m fine.
i can breathe and take my meds.
i can journal and exercise and tell myself the truth.
but at night it all comes back.
too tired to reason with myself, i experience it all again, and again, and again.
i just want to sleep.
but i cannot.
i cannot forget the way his voice sounds.
i cannot forget the way he slept beside me.
i cannot forget the way his body felt against mine.
i cannot unlove him, and it’s killing me. #metoo #experimental #healingwithart #silvergelatin #seleniumtone

greetings saints! “or do you not know that your body is a temple of the holy spirit within you, whom you have from god? you are not your own,” 1 corinthians‬ ‭6:19‬ ‭esv. we must know that are‬‬ bodies are a holy place. god tells us to be holy. why? because our maker is holy. we cannot be anything less than holy if we are in christ. the holy spirit of god can only reside in a holy place. because god’s holy spirit lives in us, our bodies become the temple of the lord. which makes us the keepers of the temple. our job is to keep god’s temple clean! the bible says: “do you not know that you are god's temple and that god's spirit dwells in you? if anyone destroys god's temple, god will destroy him. for god's temple is holy, and you are that temple.” 1 corinthians‬ ‭3:16-17‬ ‭esv‬‬. respect yourself, protect your temple, keep it holy and the king of glory shall come in, amen!

text:
‘time to unwind’

as i start unwinding into christmas and the new year festivities, i feel my whole mental approach change. 
my diary is already bursting for 2019, and that’s great. but i also need to give myself a break, step back for a few days to enjoy my time with my family, friends, and of course my daughter. 
life is precious to us all. i don’t like regrets, so i enjoy my ‘time out’ with my personal life. i recognise the importance of down time and that factoring it into my life is essential for my all round performance. 
i can’t wait to start 2019, and enjoy the opportunities coming my way, but equally i can’t wait to open presents with my daughter on christmas morning. 
so i will hit the pause button soon and finish up next week. i will enjoy my time off but make sure my diary is super tight and organised before i head off to see what santa has for me. i will liaise with all of my january clients, contacts and meetings to ensure i’m up to date and ready before i hit pause.

in essence, i will make sure i am mentally, emotionally and physically in the best shape to start 2019. that’s why i need ‘me time’. www.emmajanetaylor.life

text: “the last time i was here, grandpa, my sister and i were walking back over there toward the woods and witnessed a massive drug deal. it was the only time i’ve ever been really frightened by strangers. we were minding our own business, but these creeps kept staring at us. it really freaked me out, especially when one of the guys followed us back down the hill after we left. i will always remember that. he was in a sports coupe with the license plate “2wild4u”. as soon as we left the park, he slowly drove behind us all the way down the hill to one of those houses down there. it made the hair on the back of my neck stand up, and i couldn’t sleep for weeks. i was afraid that someone was going to come find me,” i said, retelling my story without much thought. “you were here with your grandpa and your sister? what were you wearing?” “what does that have to do with anything?” i asked, put off by the random question noah always managed to equate with sex. “because i think i was here that day. this was my park. i was in charge of distribution here and a few other places,” he said. -r. macceile 2018 now - dec 25th 100% of proceeds from my books go entirely toward my #holiday #charity #fundraiser benefiting the #afsp you can find more info on rebeccasbookshop.com candy apple butterscotch: a memoir available now! #fourstars #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor “it’s worth the read it’s about a #woman #empowered and my god that is a #wonderful thing indeed” #linkinbio #authorsofinstagram #independentpublishing #goodreads #newbookalert #readforfree

this first post is about dafne’s story (greek mythology)
dafne was so hot, she heard the single ladies were happier. but her father told her she was too sexy to be single, that maybe she could marry apolo. apolo then startet stalking her non stop, and even chased her. when she was about to be caught she begged her father to turn her into a tree, so she wouldn't have to endure apolo's hugs. even though her wish was conceded, this apollo guy wouldn't cut it out and even tried to embrace her trunk.
.
.
.
.

text:
twenty-eight years today. that is representative of a much larger, countless really, number of miracles. sometimes healing comes through the thing we are most afraid of or put off by. twenty-eight years of learning to trust, receive, serve, laugh .... love really does save the day, when it’s expressed in action. love isn’t attraction or butterflies in the stomach or getting your own way. it’s not in expensive jewelry or thrilling trips or a nice house or great sex or anything there’s an advertisement for. it’s in patience, kindness, serving, helping, burden-sharing, mercy, and grace. ... .
.
.
it is okay to love and be loved. you are worth loving, and you are capable of real love. is it scary? yes. sometimes terrifying. but most good things that change your life are. .
.
.
here’s to 28 years with my ride-or-die, and here’s to you as you heal and choose to open back up. “....what hindered love will only become part of your story.” (steffany gretzinger, “come out of hiding”) .
.
.

twenty-eight years today. that is representative of a much larger, countless really, number of miracles. sometimes healing comes through the thing we are most afraid of or put off by. twenty-eight years of learning to trust, receive, serve, laugh .... love really does save the day, when it’s expressed in action. love isn’t attraction or butterflies in the stomach or getting your own way. it’s not in expensive jewelry or thrilling trips or a nice house or great sex or anything there’s an advertisement for. it’s in patience, kindness, serving, helping, burden-sharing, mercy, and grace. ... .
.
.
it is okay to love and be loved. you are worth loving, and you are capable of real love. is it scary? yes. sometimes terrifying. but most good things that change your life are. .
.
.
here’s to 28 years with my ride-or-die, and here’s to you as you heal and choose to open back up. “....what hindered love will only become part of your story.” (steffany gretzinger, “come out of hiding”) .
.
.

text:
2018.12.15 - sat 十一月初九

銀色奇幻建築亮相台北101
lv路易威登「時空•錦•囊」展六大主題亮點 
窺見160年時尚藝術之旅

銀色亮面建築映照著台北101閃爍高樓燈光，這裡不是什麼全新聖誕市集，而是法國百年奢華品牌路易威登（louis vuitton）所打造的「時空•錦•囊time capsule taipei」展覽空間。從路易威登先生從1854年創作第一個行李箱以來，到1911年那震驚全世界的「鐵達尼號」沉船事件，lv行李箱竟在海中打撈上岸時毫髮無傷，再到近年與藝術家大玩跨界

至今發展超過160年歷史的lv，花瓣、星星和經典「monogram」logo搭上深茶色基底，其時尚形象早已眾人皆知，然而其背後又有哪些鮮為人知的時尚故事呢？適逢lv來台灣拓點35周年，品牌特地在台北101水舞廣場獻上「時空•錦•囊」展，藉由經典行李箱設計、服裝、互動式體驗，用最具lv的時尚方式闡述品項精彩歷史

此次「時空•錦•囊」展共分為六大主題區，除了彰顯lv百年來不斷求新求變的藝術想像力，更同樣凸顯了品牌勇於突破的創新力與挑戰。首先登場的「工藝展演」，當你踏進宛若穿梭大空艙門的入口後，法國工匠正現場實做示範lv製作行李箱的匠心工藝，從嚴格篩選面料材質，到細心地縫製、敲打至完工，讓時尚迷們能近距離見識到職人精湛技術

緊接著，「開啟經典之門」展區則讓大家看見最為經典的lv皮箱設計，身為19世紀貴族名門的路易威登先生，當初在整理行李時，發現拱蓋箱子難以收疊，因而發揮巧思製作出了造型方正的行李箱，邊框金屬設計不僅防撞更能防水，而此舉也成了日後lv最為標幟的設計；在此區，由設計師marcel wanders所打造的objets nomades系列lounge chair，則以品牌於1885年問世的bed trunk鋅製睡床行李箱為靈感，創造出具摩登曲線的天藍色摺疊床

精彩旅程 遨遊天下」區則將lv歷年來不斷研制劃時代行李箱用品為主，像是專為火車旅行用的行李箱，以及汽車發明後所推出的汽車行李箱設計，窺探lv是如何滿足新交通運輸形式的需求與嶄新變革，而台北101旗艦店開幕時所推出的茶杯組行李箱，也於此展區再度重現

在「雋永時尚」區，則是展現lv的時尚品味，如何讓人「時尚的旅行」，其中像是專為莎朗史東訂製的化妝箱、黑膠行李箱等皆極為吸睛；奧斯卡影后艾瑪史東（emma stone）今年響應「#metoo」活動亮相金球獎所穿著的蕾絲黑色禮服也一併展出

多年來，不間斷與草間彌生、村上隆、川久保玲、傑夫昆斯（jeff koons）和普立茲克獎建築大師frank gehry等各領域巨擘玩跨界創意的lv，則於「路易威登與藝術」區展示集大成精華之最，不但有大眾熟悉的櫻桃包外，更有替張艾嘉訂製的行李箱組，以及歌后鄧麗君熱愛的speedy包

最後，來到「魔幻行李箱」展區，則讓靜態的展示轉化為數位動態，有如一秒闖進lv所構築的時尚異想世界中，不僅能見到經典monogram文化符碼投射在行李箱外，被繽紛星空影像牆圍繞的展區，更讓人感受虛與實的華麗視覺效果，彷若「時空•錦•囊」效果達到極致

日期：107年12月15日至108年1月6日 
每日開放時間: 11:00am – 9:00pm
免費參觀

圖：謝佳見先生臉書、lavie行動家

2018.12.15 - sat 十一月初九

銀色奇幻建築亮相台北101
lv路易威登「時空•錦•囊」展六大主題亮點 
窺見160年時尚藝術之旅

銀色亮面建築映照著台北101閃爍高樓燈光，這裡不是什麼全新聖誕市集，而是法國百年奢華品牌路易威登（louis vuitton）所打造的「時空•錦•囊time capsule taipei」展覽空間。從路易威登先生從1854年創作第一個行李箱以來，到1911年那震驚全世界的「鐵達尼號」沉船事件，lv行李箱竟在海中打撈上岸時毫髮無傷，再到近年與藝術家大玩跨界

至今發展超過160年歷史的lv，花瓣、星星和經典「monogram」logo搭上深茶色基底，其時尚形象早已眾人皆知，然而其背後又有哪些鮮為人知的時尚故事呢？適逢lv來台灣拓點35周年，品牌特地在台北101水舞廣場獻上「時空•錦•囊」展，藉由經典行李箱設計、服裝、互動式體驗，用最具lv的時尚方式闡述品項精彩歷史

此次「時空•錦•囊」展共分為六大主題區，除了彰顯lv百年來不斷求新求變的藝術想像力，更同樣凸顯了品牌勇於突破的創新力與挑戰。首先登場的「工藝展演」，當你踏進宛若穿梭大空艙門的入口後，法國工匠正現場實做示範lv製作行李箱的匠心工藝，從嚴格篩選面料材質，到細心地縫製、敲打至完工，讓時尚迷們能近距離見識到職人精湛技術

text:
there is still time to order the the sacred sexuality love elixir for your holiday baes. yes. yes. yes. my baby bird is heading to the post office monday morning & probably every day this week, sending out tiny vessels of ecstasy to you & yours. i know you wanna. you know you wanna. jump in the river. it is waiting for you. i have been told that the elixir is me in a bottle. ummmmmm . . flattery will get you everywhere 😈 & i am also thinking you might need me right now. not to be presumptuous but i have been thinking of you a lot & i do have something for you.
.

text:
although william kentridge’s works are glaringly poignant, the viewer must use his/her instinctive reaction and interpretive skill to find meaning in his work. using film, animation, drawing, sculpture and performance, he transmutes political events into powerful allegories. having created politically charged artworks on the themes of apartheid for a large part of his life, his works and sentiments fit perfectly with theme of this year’s kochi-muziris biennale, ‘possibility of a non-alienated life’, as a large part of the theme entails reacting to social injustice and prejudice. here’s a look at some of his work on view at the kochi-muziris biennale. 
image credits, @kochibiennale
name: Art Fervour
tweet_full:
although william kentridge’s works are glaringly poigt, the viewer must use his/her instinctive reaction and interpretive skill to find meaning in his work. using film, animation, drawing, sculpture and performance, he transmutes political events into powerful allegories. having created politically charged artworks on the themes of apartheid for a large part of his life, his works and sentiments fit perfectly with theme of this year’s kochi-muziris biennale, ‘possibility of a non-alienated life’, as a large part of the theme entails reacting to social injustice and prejudice. here’s a look at some of his work on view at the kochi-muziris biennale. 
image credits, @kochibiennale

text:
swipe to watch full video.
this is currently one of the greatest atrocities and oppression taking place in the world today yet still it is one of the most least talked about issues. it's like the world doesn't care. it's possible there are over 2 million #uyghur #muslims who've been sent to these concentration camps which the #chinese government calls education camps. people are tortured and brain washed in these camps and the goal is to remove their cultural and religious identities. the goal is to remove #islam and religion from their hearts.
.
many of the little kids end up being orphaned and sent to government run orphanages and once again they are brainwashed and their cultural and religious identities are completely removed. many of their parents don't make it out alive from the camps due to torture. and those that have come out alive you can hear many of the witness statements of how they were tortured and what really went on in these camps. china sees the #islamic identity of the uyghur muslims as a disease or an illness. it's beyond belief what's happening in east turkestan to our uyghur #muslim brothers and sisters.
.
people can be arrested for the smallest of reasons and everything is under full surveillance. they have facial recognition cameras in the streets and have deployed so many security officers and high tech technology to keep full control or east turkestan. in their own promotional video for the 're-education camps' they had 5 high tech cameras in a single classroom. idk about you but i've never been to school or college and had 5 cameras in my class tracking my every move and every step. people's phones are taken and checked out for any suspicious religious content. there are even occasions where uyghur muslim girls have been forced to marry chinese men. i know this probably happens more often but it has been recorded on a few occasions and they even have a government strategy promoting this inter-marriage between uyghur and han chinese men. there's so much more going on and even stuff that we don't know that it's hard to say. keep them in your prayers .

＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。

text:
.
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール 公式ブランドサイト
www.laleistanbul.com
.
onlinestore、twitter、facebookのフォローもどうぞ宜しくお願いいたします。
